ReflectIgnoreClassFields - Annotation Type in org.azeckoski.reflectutils.annotations
Indicate fields on a class which should be ignored when performing class field operations
This is primarily for indicating that reflection operations should not affect fields in classes which you are extending or constant fields in interfaces
For example:
Given a class with 3 String fields: name, email, phone
Adding the annotation like so to the class will cause the phone field to not be counted for field reflection operations: @ReflectIgnoreClassFields("phone") public class Person { String name; String email; String phone; ... } And this annotation would cause the email and phone fields to be ignored: @ReflectIgnoreClassFields({"phone","email"}) public class Person { String name; String email; String phone; ... }

It also has 1 other field: String name;
